---
const properties = [
  {
    icon: '✓',
    text: 'Node compromise doesn\'t affect enforcement',
    color: 'emerald',
  },
  {
    icon: '✓',
    text: 'DPDK provides a dedicated high-throughput packet dataplane',
    color: 'emerald',
  },
  {
    icon: '✓',
    text: 'Can replace NAT gateway or cloud firewall egress paths',
    color: 'emerald',
  },
  {
    icon: '✓',
    text: 'Audit mode lets you tune policy before enforcing it',
    color: 'emerald',
  },
];

const integrations = [
  'Runs adjacent to Kubernetes as dedicated network infrastructure',
  'Compatible CNI configurations preserve source IP visibility at the gateway',
  'Overlay designs that hide pod source IPs are not currently supported',
];
---

<section class="relative py-24 border-t border-slate-800 bg-slate-900/70">
  <!-- Diamond pattern overlay -->
  <!-- <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-diamonds-radial pointer-events-none" aria-hidden="true"></div> -->
  <div class="relative mx-auto max-w-6xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="text-center max-w-3xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold text-white">
        How It Works
      </h2>
      <p class="mt-4 text-xl text-slate-400">
        External enforcement that scales
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Architecture Diagram -->
    <div class="mt-12 bg-slate-900 rounded-xl border border-slate-700 p-8">
      <h3 class="text-sm font-medium text-slate-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-6">Deployment Architecture</h3>

      <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-[1fr_auto_1fr_auto_1fr] gap-4 items-center">
        <!-- Workload Node -->
        <div class="p-4 rounded-lg border-2 border-slate-600 bg-slate-800">
          <div class="text-xs text-slate-500 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">Workload Node</div>
          <div class="space-y-2">
            <div class="p-2 rounded bg-slate-700 text-sm text-slate-300">Pod (App)</div>
            <div class="p-2 rounded bg-slate-700 text-sm text-slate-300">Pod (API)</div>
            <div class="p-2 rounded bg-slate-700 text-sm text-slate-300">Pod Network</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Arrow -->
        <div class="hidden lg:flex flex-col items-center text-slate-500">
          <span class="text-2xl">→</span>
          <span class="text-xs mt-1">all egress</span>
        </div>
        <div class="lg:hidden flex justify-center text-slate-500">
          <span class="text-2xl">↓</span>
        </div>

        <!-- Egress Gateway -->
        <div class="p-4 rounded-lg border-2 border-brand-500 bg-brand-900">
          <div class="text-xs text-brand-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">Egress Gateway</div>
          <div class="space-y-2">
            <div class="p-2 rounded bg-brand-800 text-sm text-white">DPDK Dataplane</div>
            <div class="p-2 rounded bg-brand-800 text-sm text-white">Policy Engine</div>
            <div class="p-2 rounded bg-brand-800 text-sm text-white">DNS Proxy</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Arrow -->
        <div class="hidden lg:flex flex-col items-center text-slate-500">
          <span class="text-2xl">→</span>
          <span class="text-xs mt-1">allowed</span>
        </div>
        <div class="lg:hidden flex justify-center text-slate-500">
          <span class="text-2xl">↓</span>
        </div>

        <!-- Internet -->
        <div class="p-4 rounded-lg border border-slate-700 bg-slate-800">
          <div class="text-xs text-slate-500 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">Destinations</div>
          <div class="space-y-2">
            <div class="p-2 rounded bg-emerald-950 text-sm text-emerald-400 border border-emerald-800">*.github.com</div>
            <div class="p-2 rounded bg-emerald-950 text-sm text-emerald-400 border border-emerald-800">api.stripe.com</div>
            <div class="p-2 rounded bg-red-950 text-sm text-red-400 border border-red-800 line-through">evil.com ✗</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="mt-6 text-sm text-slate-400 text-center">
        The gateway runs on a separate security boundary from your workloads — compromising a workload node does not compromise enforcement.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Key Properties -->
    <div class="mt-12 grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
      <div>
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white mb-4">Key Properties</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-3">
          {properties.map((prop) => (
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-5 h-5 rounded-full bg-emerald-900 flex items-center justify-center mt-0.5">
                <svg class="w-3 h-3 text-emerald-400" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
                  <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="3" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7" />
                </svg>
              </div>
              <span class="text-slate-300">{prop.text}</span>
            </li>
          ))}
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white mb-4">Integration</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-3">
          {integrations.map((item) => (
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-5 h-5 rounded-full bg-slate-700 flex items-center justify-center mt-0.5">
                <svg class="w-3 h-3 text-slate-400" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
                  <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 5l7 7-7 7" />
                </svg>
              </div>
              <span class="text-slate-400">{item}</span>
            </li>
          ))}
        </ul>

        <div class="mt-6 p-4 rounded-lg bg-slate-800 border border-slate-700">
          <p class="text-sm text-slate-400">
            <span class="text-white font-medium">Deployment model:</span> treat the gateway as dedicated network infrastructure outside the workload node.
            For Kubernetes, compatibility depends on pod source IPs staying visible to the gateway.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
